OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy but largely dry during
OL,6,Fthe morning, before a slow-moving band
OL,7,Fof rain gradually moves eastwards
OL,8,Fduring the afternoon, fragmenting as
OL,9,Fit does so. Breezy.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FCloudy overnight and dry,
OL,12,Fwith some occasional breaks in the
OL,13,Fcloud, allowing the temperatures to
OL,14,Ffall with widespread frost. Winds
OL,15,Fbecoming light and variable.
OL,16,
OL,17,CTuesday:FAfter a frosty start, Tuesday
OL,18,Fwill be dry with some sunny spells and
OL,19,Flight winds. Cloud will slowly thicken
OL,20,Facross the region by the evening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
